## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Deployment credentials needed**: When we reach the deployment phase, I will need you to:
> 1. Authenticate with **GitHub** to push to a new repository
> 2. Authenticate with **Vercel** to deploy the frontend
> 3. Authenticate with **Render** to deploy the backend
>
> I will prompt you at that point — no action needed now.

> [!NOTE]
> The existing app only uses **TF-IDF + Cosine Similarity** (no external AI/LLM APIs), so **no API keys** are needed for the core functionality. The app is fully self-contained.

## Verification Plan

### Automated — Backend API Test
1. Start the backend: `cd backend && pip install -r requirements.txt && uvicorn main:app --reload`
2. Test health endpoint: `curl http://localhost:8000/api/health`
3. Test analyze endpoint with a sample PDF:
   ```bash
   curl -X POST http://localhost:8000/api/analyze \
     -F "file=@test_resume.pdf" \
     -F "job_description=python developer with experience in machine learning"
   ```
4. Verify JSON response has [score](file:///c:/Users/chira/OneDrive/Desktop/AI-Resume-Reviewer-ATS-Analyzer-main/components/results.py#4-12), `label`, `feedback` fields

### Automated — Frontend Build
1. `cd frontend && npm install && npm run build` — verify no TypeScript/build errors

### Manual — End-to-End Browser Test
1. Start backend on port 8000, frontend on port 3000
2. Open `http://localhost:3000` in browser
3. Upload a PDF resume
4. Paste a job description
5. Click "Analyze Match"
6. Verify: loading state appears → results display with score, gauge, and feedback
7. Verify: responsive layout works on mobile viewport
8. Verify: error states work (no file, no JD, invalid file type)
